<subSubSection box="[151,1062,438,465]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,438,1077]" box="[151,1062,438,465]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,173,438,464]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Grouvelle, 1899: 127" authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityPageNumber="127" authorityYear="1899" box="[179,547,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[179,305,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cillaeopsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Grouvelle, A." box="[312,547,439,465]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="125 - 133" refId="ref104943" refString="Grouvelle, A. (1899) Nitidulides de l'Afrique occidentale (Cameroun) recoltes par M. I. Conradt. Annales de la Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 68, 125 - 133." type="journal article" year="1899">Grouvelle, 1899: 127</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
—Afrotropical Region (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirejtshuk, A. G." box="[864,1050,439,465]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="17 - 89" refId="ref106131" refString="Kirejtshuk, A. G. (2001) Notes on the systematics of the African Nitidulidae (Coleoptera). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 93, 17 - 89." type="journal article" year="2001">Kirejtshuk 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,438,1077]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1899" box="[249,375,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[249,375,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cillaeopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was initially proposed as a separate genus with two species, “genre voisin des 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[1249,1409,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Orthogramma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1249,1409,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Orthogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirejtshuk" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[151,244,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,244,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cillaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” which differs from these genera in the “abdomen supra quatuor segmentis ultimis expositis” (
<bibRefCitation author="Grouvelle, A." pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="125 - 133" refId="ref104943" refString="Grouvelle, A. (1899) Nitidulides de l'Afrique occidentale (Cameroun) recoltes par M. I. Conradt. Annales de la Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 68, 125 - 133." type="journal article" year="1899">Grouvelle 1899: 127</bibRefCitation>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Grouvelle, 1899" authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1899" box="[281,684,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kraatzi">
<emphasis box="[281,493,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cillaeopsis kraatzi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Grouvelle, A." box="[501,684,547,573]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="125 - 133" refId="ref104943" refString="Grouvelle, A. (1899) Nitidulides de l'Afrique occidentale (Cameroun) recoltes par M. I. Conradt. Annales de la Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 68, 125 - 133." type="journal article" year="1899">Grouvelle, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Grouvelle, 1899" authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1899" box="[741,1057,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidula">
<emphasis box="[741,862,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. nitidula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Grouvelle, A." box="[870,1057,547,573]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="125 - 133" refId="ref104943" refString="Grouvelle, A. (1899) Nitidulides de l'Afrique occidentale (Cameroun) recoltes par M. I. Conradt. Annales de la Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 68, 125 - 133." type="journal article" year="1899">Grouvelle, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). Among other things 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1899" box="[1310,1436,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1310,1436,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cillaeopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by the eyes located at the head base. However, the third species (
<emphasis box="[1105,1314,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cilaeopsis maynei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Grouvelle, A." pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="130 - 142" refId="ref105191" refString="Grouvelle, A. (1914 c) Clavicornes du Museo du Congo. Revue zoologique africaine, 4, 130 - 142." type="journal article" year="1914">Grouvelle 1914c: 129</bibRefCitation>
) should be regarded in composition of the genus 
<emphasis box="[845,1013,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Paracilaeopsis</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1021,1130,619,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1021,1130,619,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kirejtshuk, A. G." box="[1145,1331,619,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="17 - 89" refId="ref106131" refString="Kirejtshuk, A. G. (2001) Notes on the systematics of the African Nitidulidae (Coleoptera). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 93, 17 - 89." type="journal article" year="2001">Kirejtshuk 2001</bibRefCitation>
) because its eyes are located at distance from the head base and abdominal segment 4 is not completely exposed from under elytral apices (this species is known to the first author after the specimens from collections of 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1244,1309,690,716]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">SDEI</emphasis>
and Royal Museum for Central Africa in Tervuren (
<collectingCountry box="[598,700,727,754]" name="Belgium" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Belgium</collectingCountry>
)). Many characters of the initial members of 
<emphasis box="[1194,1312,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cilaeopsis</emphasis>
mentioned in their original descriptions, except for convexity of body and comparatively shorter elytra, can fit to those in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,307,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeopeplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,307,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cillaeopeplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Moreover, the species similar to Hawaiian and Australian members of this genus are rather frequent among African cillaeines (see the below notes on distribution of 
<taxonomicName box="[892,1048,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeopeplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[892,1048,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cillaeopeplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Taking into consideration of the body convexity and the reminiscence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[595,755,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Orthogramma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[595,755,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Orthogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicated by the descriptor it can be supposed some similarity of 
<emphasis box="[181,299,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cilaeopsis</emphasis>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1880" box="[363,517,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Xanthopeplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[363,517,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Xanthopeplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than with other described African cillaeines. 
<bibRefCitation author="Grouvelle, A." box="[1098,1292,907,933]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="125 - 133" refId="ref104943" refString="Grouvelle, A. (1899) Nitidulides de l'Afrique occidentale (Cameroun) recoltes par M. I. Conradt. Annales de la Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 68, 125 - 133." type="journal article" year="1899">Grouvelle (1899)</bibRefCitation>
indicated on the similarity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1899" box="[339,465,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[339,465,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cillaeopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[531,691,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Orthogramma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[531,691,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Orthogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and four last abdominal segments (probably completely) exposed from under elytral apices (some species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[636,757,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Ithyphenes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[636,757,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ithyphenes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have abdominal segment 4 completely uncovered by elytra, for example 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev, 2022" authorityName="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev" authorityYear="2022" box="[292,527,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Ithyphenes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectifrons" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[292,527,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ithyphenes rectifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[533,622,1015,1041]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[533,622,1015,1041]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Thus, the initial members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1899" box="[966,1092,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[966,1092,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cillaeopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
need to be examined to clarify their reasonable placement in the subfamily.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
